  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patient with severe persistent asthma already treated

          2. Patient with history of asthma &gt; 1 year prior to screening visit

          3. Patient with no significant change in the regular asthma medication, no severe asthma
             exacerbation for at least 4 weeks prior to screening visit

          4. Non-smoker patient for at least one year and with a prior tobacco consumption &lt; 10
             packs a year

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Asthmatic patient still exposed to allergens or to triggering factors influencing
             asthma control

          2. Patient with history of acute infectious sinusitis or respiratory tract infection
             within 4 weeks prior to screening

          3. Patient presenting with cardiac disorders

          4. Patient with active lung disease other than asthma
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
